  "text": "The proof follows by adapting the arguments in [CITATION_1] to the two-dimensional case. Because these authors discuss the case where the bandwidths h r and h d are of the same order, i.e. lim n→∞ h r /h d = c > 0, and in order to make the present paper self-contained, we present some details, which are also useful to see why the bandwidth conditions in (3.1) -(3.4) are required. Moreover, the arguments given in this subsection will help the reader to understand the proof of Theorem 3.3. We use Lemma 2.1, h d = o(h r ), and the decomposition ∆ n (t|y) = (m",
